{"sections":[],"relationshipsSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/ShapeStyle","doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/s8CopyableP","doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/s8SendableP"],"kind":"relationships","title":"Conforms To","type":"conformsTo"}],"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"minor":3,"major":0},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI"]]},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"Material"}],"platforms":["macOS"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"overview","text":"Overview","type":"heading","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"You can apply a blur effect to a view that appears behind another view by","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"adding a material with the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"View\/background(_:ignoresSafeAreaEdges:)"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"modifier:","type":"text"}]},{"code":["ZStack {","    Color.teal","    Label(\"Flag\", systemImage: \"flag.fill\")","        .padding()","        .background(.regularMaterial)","}"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"In the example above, the ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/ZStack","type":"reference"},{"text":" layers a ","type":"text"},{"code":"Label","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" on top of the color","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/ShapeStyle\/teal","type":"reference"},{"text":". The background modifier inserts the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"regular material below the label, blurring the part of","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the background that the label — including its padding — covers:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A material isn’t a view, but adding a material is like inserting a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"translucent layer between the modified view and its background:"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The blurring effect provided by the material isn’t simple opacity. Instead,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"it uses a platform-specific blending that produces an effect that resembles","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"heavily frosted glass. You can see this more easily with a complex","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"background, like an image:","type":"text"}]},{"code":["ZStack {","    Image(\"chili_peppers\")","        .resizable()","        .aspectRatio(contentMode: .fit)","    Label(\"Flag\", systemImage: \"flag.fill\")","        .padding()","        .background(.regularMaterial)","}"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"For physical materials, the degree to which the background colors pass","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"through depends on the thickness. The effect also varies with light and","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"dark appearance:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If you need a material to have a particular shape, you can use the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"View\/background(_:in:fillStyle:)","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" modifier. For example, you can"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"create a material with rounded corners:"}]},{"code":["ZStack {","    Color.teal","    Label(\"Flag\", systemImage: \"flag.fill\")","        .padding()","        .background(.regularMaterial, in: RoundedRectangle(cornerRadius: 8))","}"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"When you add a material, foreground elements exhibit vibrancy,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"a context-specific blend of the foreground and background colors"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"that improves contrast. However using "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/View\/foregroundStyle(_:)","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to set a custom foreground style — excluding the hierarchical styles,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"like "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/ShapeStyle\/secondary-swift.type.property","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" — disables vibrancy."}]},{"style":"note","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"A material blurs a background that’s part of your app, but not","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"what appears behind your app on the screen.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"For example, the content on the Home Screen doesn’t affect the appearance","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"of a widget.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"type":"aside","name":"Note"}]}],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/openswiftui\/material"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Material"},"abstract":[{"text":"A background material type.","type":"text"}],"topicSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Material\/ShapeStyle-Implementations"],"title":"Default Implementations","generated":true,"anchor":"Default-Implementations"}],"kind":"symbol","metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"OpenSwiftUI"}],"remoteSource":{"url":"https:\